snippet.textDisplay: There is no such thing as an "addictive personality". Things are ADDICTIVE and that is that. Those people who use the term "addictive personality" and believe it is a trait that leads to addiction are doing something VERY dangerous. It tells people who haven't yet experienced addiction to something that they'll be ok with something addictive because they "don't have an addictive personality". This is a lie. EVERYONE is able to become addicted to something and EVERYONE usually is... sugar, morning coffee, wine with dinner, beer after work, food, drugs, exercise, YOUR PHONE USE... so PLEASE, stop saying "addictive personality". It is DOPAMINE in the brain, adrenaline, seratonin etc which is the link to addiction... not a personality trait. There is no "type" to get addicted. Anyone who truly understands that knows that EVERYONE can get addicted... it's not a trait.
